### <span id="52"></span>52.

   At that time the venerable Upananda, of the Sakya tribe, had two
novices, Ka*nd*aka and Mahaka; these committed sodomy with each other.
The Bhikkhus were annoyed, &c.: 'How can novices abandon themselves to
such bad conduct?'

   They told this thing to the Blessed One, &c.

   'Let no one, O Bhikkhus, ordain two novices. He who does, is guilty
of a dukka*t*a offence<span id="page_205_fr_1"></span>[<sup><span
class="small">1</span></sup>](#page_205_note_1.md).'

