is said that, if the upasampadâ ordination had been conferred, against
the rule, on a person that has not yet attained his twentieth year, the
upa*ggh*âya has made himself guilty of a pâ*k*ittiya offence, the
â*k*ariya and the other present Bhikkhus only of a dukka*t*a offence. We
